Nagafen was killed on 9-22 as scheduled.<br>
Fumin's 9-21 raid on Vox went down in a blaze of glory... with VOX STILL UP.  <br>
<br>
WE ARE RAIDING VOX for Monday 9-23  9:00pm EST.<br>
<br>
We are in need of clerics, an enchanter, wizards, and a druid Lev 52+. Please spread the word<br>
<br>
 -------- /EDIT --------------<br>
<br>
MONDAY 9:00pm EST [ 8:00pm Central, 7:00pm Mountain, 6:00pm PST ] Everfrost Entrance to Permafrost. [ Easier to port as one to Lavastorm, than vice versa.]<br>
<br>
As discussed on the Fellowship message boards earlier, it is high time both Nagafen and VOX went down every week. To that end I am testing out leading a Fellowship raid on every Monday night on whichever dragon is still standing just prior to Tuesday morning patch.<br>
<br>
For this week there are Scheduled raids on Lady Vox 9-21 Noon EST, and Nagafen 9-22 8pm EST. If either of these raids fails to kill its intended target, this raid will take that dragon.<br>
<br>
THERE WILL BE NO RESERVED ITEMS FOR THIS RAID.<br>
<br>
<br>
REQUIRED RAID PERSONEL:<br>
<br>
One level 52 Warrior for MA, 3 Clerics (one must be Lev 52+), 2-3 Monks for pulling, 3+ Paladins, 2 Enchanters (one must be lev 52+), one Shaman lev 49+, one druid Lev 52+. <br>
<br>
Getting people killed IS NOT my goal here, if essential raid personnel are not signed up by the raid date, it will be canceled; please check here on the date of the raid for cancellations. <br>
<br>
Immeasurable thanks to Findra for advice on Vox and Nagafen raids. Should Hipo be present on any raid I lead Hipo may roll as a warrior instead of a cleric on Findra’s behalf.<br>
<br>
Druids and Wizards signing up, please be prepared to port people 30-60 minutes before the start time - thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Don't be late! I will be putting groups together at 9:00pm EST. Sign-ups get priority, but expect to have final groups announced at about 9:10pm EST. <br>
<br>
HOW TO GET THERE<br>
1. Closest Druid portal: Surefall Glades<br>
2. Closest Wizard portal: SE corner of West Karana<br>
<br>
I will be supping peridots for buffs. If you want a TL out at the end, make sure your destination doesn't require a TL stone, or have one to give to the wizzy.<br>
<br>
I highly recommend everyone take measures to reduce lag - nothing sucks worse than going LD right as everyone charges the dragon (possibly the highest lag moment of the raid).<br>
<br>
There will be NO GATING during the raid. If anyone gates out at any time, for any reason they are booted from the raid. Don't even have the spell memorized. If you fall in the lava, in a pit in permafrost, get massive aggro, whatever - you die. You will get rez'd (almost guaranteed 90% or better), and the raid will continue. If you gate out, you WILL train the raid when you come back. That is why I do not allow gating.<br>
<br>
