********** Chat Channels ********** <br>
<br>
Please use the following chat channels:<br>
<br>
FWRAID - raid wide chat<br>
FWLISTEN - important announcements only. This is where I talk, MA posts messages, snarers announce when snares land, etc. NO CHAT HERE.<br>
FWLEAD - all group leaders (first toon listed for each group) and raid leaders will communicate here. Please use chain of command whenever possible (toons -&gt; group leaders -&gt; raid leaders)<br>
<br>
********** Floorplan **************** <br>
<br>
Go to www.eqatlas.com and familiarize yourself with the layout of both lairs. MEMORIZE BOTH MAPS. For Nagafen [ Nagafens Lair (aka Sol B) ]. For Vox [ Permafrost Keep ]<br>
<br>
STAGING PHASE<br>
1. When you are in Everfrost report in to the raid leader.<br>
2. The raid leader may tell you if the raid is short of certain classes. Check with friends if asked.<br>
3. Turn off anonymous when you show up.<br>
4. The raid leader, pullers, and group Leaders will use FWLISTEN channel. All other communication should be on the FWRAID channel.<br>
5. It may take a while for the raid leader to work out final groups and the attack plan, especially if the raid is short of people in critical areas (clerics, enchanters, bards, and nukers).<br>
<br>
At all times do not move further forwards than your raid leader unless you are a designated puller.<br>
<br>
************ Resist Gear ************<br>
<br>
Try to acquire as much Fire and cold resist gear as possible, mages present will summon the appropriate +15 fire /cold resist all/all shoulder gear.<br>
<br>
Naggy's most deadly weapon is his AE fire breath and AE fear spell. Wear as much MR/FR gear as possible; sacrifice all other statistics (yes, even AC) to get these as high as possible.<br>
<br>
If you don't have much, consider acquiring: 2xEarring of Fire Reflection (AC1 FR5 ~26pp at Lavastorm gypsies), Gold Diamond Mask (FR10 CR10 MR3), Gold Hermatite Necklace (FR7), Gold Emerald Bracelet (AC4 FR6), Platinum Emerald Ring (AC4 FR10), Hand Woven Legging (AC8 FR10), Rune Boned Fork (MR10 CR10 FR10), and Crown of the Froglok King (AC12 CR20 FR20).<br>
<br>
Vox's most deadly weapon is her AE cold breath and AE fear spell. Wear as much MR/CR gear as possible; sacrifice all other statistics (yes, even AC) to get these as high as possible. If you are level 52, CR gear is more important that MR gear, because you will resist most of her fears if you have a bard in your group.<br>
<br>
If you don't have much, consider acquiring: 2xPlatinum Peridot Ring (AC4 CR10), Cloak of the Icebear (AC8 HP10 CR20), Rune Boned Fork (MR10 CR10 FR10), Crown of the Froglok King (AC12 CR20 FR20), Velium Round Shield (AC15 CR10), and Gnomish Environmental Suit (AC9 FR10 CR10 PR10). There are a wealth of other items available, especially with the addition of SoV.<br>
4. Many of the mobs in Permafrost have high cold resist - including Vox, use fire based spells where possible for minimum resists.<br>
<br>
Make sure both sets of resist equipment are easily accessible in one or two packs when you arrive.<br>
<br>
